@NODE Introduction

	SwazBlanker/Introduction
	========================

	SwazBlanker is a modular screen/mouse blanker providing the
	following fetures:

		o  Blanking of the screen when computer is inactive

		o  Blanking of the mouse pointer when you are typing

		o  Screen can be blanked by pressing a hotkey

		o  Several different blanker modules are provided

		o  Auto-sense @{" reblanking/unblanking " LINK Reblank} when blanker
		   screen is not visible.

		o  @{" OverBlanking " LINK Overblanking} if blanker is not receiving CPU

	Other features:

	  @{" App Window          " LINK AppWin		} Drop icons into the preferences window
	  @{" Arexx               " LINK Arexx		} Send commands via arexx
	  @{" Commodities         " LINK Comodity	} Standard commodities interface
	  @{" Locale              " LINK Locale		} Interface available in different languages
	  @{" Task Management     " LINK TaskManage	} Monitoring of CPU usage of a blanker
@ENDNODE

@NODE TaskManage "Monitoring the CPU usage of a blanker..."

	SwazBlanker/Task Management
	===========================

	The blanker task is managed by SwazBlanker. If the blanker module
	uses too much CPU time or is unable to gain enough CPU time (other
	tasks at higher priority may be using it all) then SwazBlanker
	will shutdown the blanker module and perform the @{" Normal " LINK Mod_Internal_Normal	} blanking
	method of a standard blank screen.

@ENDNODE


