@NODE DefinitionOfInactivity "Definition Of Inactivity"

	SwazBlanker/Definition Of Inactivity
	====================================

	SwazBlanker defines a state of inactivity as being a failure of occurrence
	of any @{" activity " LINK DefinitionOfActivity} for a duration of
	preferred timeout.

@ENDNODE

@NODE DefinitionOfActivity "Definition Of Activity"

	SwazBlanker/Definition Of Activity
	==================================

	SwazBlanker defines a state of activity as being events such as a
	keypress or a mouse movement. If no activity occurs for the length
	of timeout as set in the preferences, then a state of @{" inactivity " LINK DefinitionOfInactivity}
	has been attained and the screen should be blanked using the
	preferred blanking method as set in the @{" listview " LINK ListView}.

@ENDNODE


