@NODE CLIArgs "Command Line Arguments and Tool Types"

	SwazBlanker/CLI Arguments and Tool Types
	========================================

	SwazBlanker accepts the following either as Command Line Arguments if
	run from CLI or as ToolTypes if you are running SwazBlanker from
	Workbench or the WBStartup drawer.

	CX_POPKEY=<string>
		This is the string describing the key combination that will
		show the SwazBlanker @{" preferences interface " LINK Config}.
		@{i}Default = None.@{ui}

	CX_POPUP=<yes|no>
		If set to YES then the SwazBlanker @{" preferences interface " LINK Config}
		will be opened as soon as SwazBlanker is run.
		@{i}Default = NO.@{ui}

	CX_PRIORITY=<number>
		This sets the priority of the commodities broker.
		@{i}Default = 0.@{ui}

	BLANKKEY=<string>
		This is the string describing the key combination that will
		tell SwazBlanker to blank the screen and mouse pointer.
		@{i}Default = Never.@{ui}

	DEFBLANKERPATH=<path>
		This sets the default path to the blanker modules. This
		gets set to where you installed the blanker modules when
		you ran the install script. The setting in @{" preferences " LINK Config}
		will override this setting.
		@{i}Default = "blankers".@{ui}

	DOCPATH=<path>
		This sets the path to the documentation. This gets set to
		where you installed the SwazBlanker documentation when you
		ran the install script.
		@{i}Default = "docs".@{ui}

	HELPFILE=<filename>
		This is the name of the help file. It will be searched for
		initially in the DOCPATH (@{i}see above@{ui}).
		@{i}Default = "SwazBlanker".@{ui}

	DELETABLEMODULES=<yes|no>
		If set to YES then then you may delete modules from your
		disk by pressing DEL in the preferences window when a module
		is selected.
		@{i}Default = NO.@{ui}


@ENDNODE



@NODE Arexx "How to use SwazBlanker via Arexx..."

	SwazBlanker/Arexx
	=================

	SwazBlanker adds an arexx port to the system named "SwazBlanker" you
	may use the following commands to control certain features:

	  BLANK            - do the preferred blank method

	  BLANK Normal     - blank using the normal blanker.

	  BLANK Random     - blank using a random blanker.

	  BLANK <filename> - blank using a specified blanker module.

	  BLANKMOUSE       - blank the mouse pointer [Not implemented]

	  DISABLE          - disable SwazBlanker [Not implemented]

	  ENABLE           - enable SwazBlanker [Not implemented]

	  HIDE             - hides the about window.

	  QUIT             - will try to remove SwazBlanker from the system.

	  SHOW             - displays the SwazBlanker about window.

	  UNBLANK          - cease blanking



	Examples:

	  o To blank the screen send the "BLANK" command:

		rx ' address SwazBlanker BLANK

	  o To un-blank the screen send the "UNBLANK" command:

		rx ' address SwazBlanker UNBLANK

	  o To show the SwazBlanker preferences interface:

		rx ' address SwazBlanker SHOW

@ENDNODE


